Most founders set goals and forget them by March. Here is a simple quarterly method that keeps you on track and moving forward.\

## The most common mistake is setting too many goals at once. Ten priorities is not a plan. It is a list of things you feel guilty about not doing.

The second mistake is vagueness. "Grow my client base" is not a goal. It is a direction. A goal needs a number, a deadline, and a clear first action. Without those three things, you are not setting a goal. You are making a wish.

The third mistake is setting goals based on what sounds impressive rather than what is actually achievable given your current time, resources, and energy. Ambitious is fine. Disconnected from reality is not
